Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoCloneFlop(25.10)                                        ecoCloneFlop(25.10)

Name
       ecoCloneFlop

Syntax
       ecoCloneFlop

       [-help]

       [-batchMode]

       [-force]

       -instances <flopInstName>

       [-max_num_loads <num_of_loads>]

       [-numClones <number>]

       [-radius <num_of_rows>]

       [-verbose]

       Clones flop instances as long as the flops meet the following criteria:

              * They are not FIXED

              * They are allowed to be resized

              * When they do not share synchronization signals with some other
                instance

       This  command is used when you want to clone a flop as manual ECO. Man-
       ual flop cloning is usually performed  on  control  signal  flip-flops,
       when  the  output  needs  to  reach  sections of the floorplan that are
       spread out. Cloning the flip-flops allows you to place each clone close
       to its sink points, thereby reducing the timing closure effort.

       This command should not be used to clone a flop  that  drives  a  clock
       net,  which  is a net with the attribute isDefInclock, because this may
       lead to problems during optimization or timing. The default behavior of
       the command may reject the flip-flop cloning due to design  constraints
       or QOR impact.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each ecoCloneFlop parameter. For  a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:  man ecoCloneFlop.

       -batchMode
              When specified, clones multiple instances at the same time  with
              no timing update in between. For example,

              ecoCloneFlop -batchMode -numClone 2 -insts {reg1 reg2}

              Both, reg1 and reg2 are cloned in the same timing session.

       -force When  specified, forces the flop instance to clone. This parame-
              ter is used when flop cloning is rejected by the software.

       -instances <flopInstName>
              Specifies the list of instances to be cloned. This is a required
              parameter.

       -max_num_loads <num_of_loads>
              Specifies that cloning should be skipped for  instances  driving
              more than the specified number of loads.

              Default: 50000

       -numClones <number>
              Specifies the cloned numbers for the flop instance.

       -radius <num_of_rows>
              Specifies  that  the  clones should be placed within a radius of
              the specified number of rows from their preferred location based
              on the original instance location and the center of mass of  the
              new set of loads.

              Default: 10

       -verbose
              When  specified,  verbose  messages  are  displayed  during  the
              cloning of flop instances.

Example
       The following command will clone the flip-flop $inst 3 times:

       ecoCloneFlop -instances $inst -numClones 3

